Police are looking for a driver of a car that hit and killed a pedestrian at Cabanas, Nairobi. The man was hit at 6 am as he crossed the busy Mombasa highway. Traffic officers have been deployed there to clear the scene. Police say they are reviewing CCTV cameras on the highway to establish the motorist behind the incident.According to NTSA, at least two pedestrians are killed on the road every week by speeding cars.Just two weeks ago, twenty people died in a road accident after a bus collided with two trailers at Mbaruk area, near Gilgil along Nakuru-Nairobi highway.Nakuru police commander Hassan Barua said the driver of the bus was overtaking a truck when he collided with an oncoming truck.Read: 20 dead, several injured in Nakuru-Nairobi accident